structured.description: An `AuthenticationController` class that acts as a RESTful API for authentication purposes. The controller receives a `LoginRequest` object from the client and passes it to an `AuthenticationService` implementation for processing. Once the authentication is successful, the controller creates and returns a `ResponseEntity` object with the user ID and JWT token in the HTTP headers.

items.description: Is a Spring REST controller that implements the AuthenticationApi interface. It provides a login method that takes a valid LoginRequest object as input and returns a ResponseEntity with the user ID and JWT token in the HTTP headers. The class also includes a private method for creating the HTTP headers based on the returned AuthenticationData object.
items.name: AuthenticationController

items.description: Authenticates a user by calling the `loginService` and returning an `ResponseEntity` with the authentication data.

params.name: loginRequest
params.description: user's login details, containing the username and password for authentication by the `authenticationService`.

returns.description: a `ResponseEntity` object with an `OK` status and headers containing authentication data.

items.name: login

items.description: Creates HTTP headers with user ID and JWT token for login purposes based on input `AuthenticationData`.

params.name: authenticationData
params.description: user's login information, providing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

returns.description: a set of HTTP headers containing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

items.name: createLoginHeaders

structured.description: A configuration class named CorsConfig that enables CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) for an application built using Spring MVC. It uses the WebMvcConfigurer interface from the spring-webmvc package to configure CORS. The allowedOrigins variable is used to specify a list of allowed origins, and the addCorsMappings method is overridden to define the CORS configuration for all URLs ("/**").

items.description: Enables cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) for an application. It specifies allowed origins, methods, headers, and credentials for incoming requests.
items.name: CorsConfig

items.description: Defines a Spring WebMvcConfigurer that enables cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) for all endpoints ("/**") by allowing specific origins, methods, and headers. It also exposes certain headers ("token", "userId") and allows credentials to be included in requests.

returns.description:
a configuration for enabling CORS.

It is an instance of `WebMvcConfigurer`, and provides mapping configurations for cross-origin requests. The `addCorsMappings` method specifies that all URLs (/***) are allowed to be accessed from any origin, using any HTTP method with any headers, exposing specific headers (token and userId), and allowing credentials.

usage.description: Note: The allowedOrigins property should be set in the application.properties or application.yml file.

items.name: corsConfigurer

items.description: Configures CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) for a web application. It allows requests from all origins, methods, and headers, exposes specific headers, and enables credentials for cross-origin requests. The configuration is applied to all resources using the `/**` pattern.

params.name: registry
params.description: configuration registry for CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) settings, allowing the specification of mapping rules and configurations for cross-origin requests.

items.name: addCorsMappings
